<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "5A">
<servcat sctnbr = "05" scnbr = "01">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "4">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70B5104015" svcinfotypenbr = "06" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Line Pressure Test
</title>
<ptxt>
Purpose of this test is to check operating conditions of each part by measuring fluid pressure in fluid pressure line.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Line pressure test requires the following conditions.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
ATF is at normal operating temperature (70 – 80 &#176;C / 158 – 176 &#176;F).
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
ATF is replenished to proper level (between FULL and LOW on dipstick).
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
A/C OFF
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Hoist vehicle.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove fluid pressure check hole bolt (1).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Attach oil pressure gauge to fluid pressure check hole (2) in transaxle case.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
After attaching oil pressure gauge, check that no fluid leakage exists.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5A004">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09925-37811-001">
09925-37811-001
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A510077.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "107.520mm" ver = "01" gw = "209" gh = "288"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Start engine and run at idle.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Depress foot brake fully, shift to “D” range, depress accelerator pedal fully to stall engine and check fluid pressure.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
In the same way, check line pressure in “R” range.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not continue running engine at stall speed for longer than 5 seconds.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
After performing line pressure test, be sure to leave engine running at idle for longer than one minute before performing another line pressure test.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<spec>
<title>
A/T line pressure
</title>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "3" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.527in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.474in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "1.474in"/>
<thead>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
“D” range
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
“R” range
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
At idle speed
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
373 – 412 kPa (3.8 – 4.2 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 54.1 – 59.9 psi, 3.73 – 4.12 bar)
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
 589 – 677 kPa (6.0 – 6.9 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 85.4 – 98.1 psi, 5.89 – 6.77 bar)
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
At stall speed
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
1,246 – 1,373 kPa (12.7 – 14.0 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 181 – 199 psi, 12.46 – 13.73 bar)
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1" valign = "middle" align = "center">
<ptxt>
1,648 – 1,903 kPa (16.8 – 19.4 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 239 – 276 psi, 16.48 – 19.03 bar)
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
If check result is OK, disconnect special tool.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
After applying ATF to new O-ring, fit it to fluid pressure check hole bolt (1). Then install fluid pressure check hole bolt to transaxle case (2) by tightening it to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T5A001">
<t-part>
Fluid pressure check hole bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
7.5
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
0.76
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
5.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A510078.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "58.391mm" ver = "01" gw = "184" gh = "149"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B5104015001" page = "1">
<title>
Troubleshooting
</title>
